title: 109_hr2677
content: CERTAIN CHEMICALS. Subchapter II of chapter 99 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended by inserting new headings. Mixtures of zinc dialkyldithiophosphate with an elastomer binder of ethylene-propylene-diene monomer and ethyl vinyl acetate, dispersing agents, and silica are provided for in subheading 3812.10.50. Mixtures of dithiocarbamate, thiazole, and thiuram are also included. Mixtures of caprolactam disulfide with an elastomer binder of ethylene-propylene-diene monomer and ethyl vinyl acetate are classified under subheading 9902.07.33. Mixtures of N-(3,4-dichloro-phenyl)-N,N-dimethylurea with acrylate rubber are classified under subheading 9902.07.34, while mixtures of zinc dicyanato are classified under subheading 9902.07.35. The curr_chunk describes the classification of 4,8-Dicyclohexyl-6-2,10-dimethyl-12H-dibenzo[d,g][1,3,2]dioxaphosphocin under subheading 9902.07.36 with no changes before 12/31/2009. The curr_chunk provides information on the classification of mixtures of Benzenesulfonic acid, dodecyl-, with 2-aminoethanol and Poly (oxy-1,2-ethanediyl), a-[(9Z)-1-oxo-9-octadecenyl]-w-hydroxy- under subheading 3402.90.50 with no changes before 12/31/2009. The curr_chunk provides details on the classification of 1,3-Dihydro-3,3-bis (4-hydroxy-m-tolyl)-2H-indol-2-one under subheading 9902.07.39 with no changes before 12/31/2009. The amendment made by subsection (a) applies to goods entered on or after the 15th day after the date of the enactment of this Act.
